EIB’s Maystadt Backs Draghi to Succeed ECB’s Trichet, Pais Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-02-27T09:52:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/eib-s-maystadt-backs-draghi-to-succeed-ecb-s-trichet-pais-says.html
Philippe Maystadt, president of the
European Investment Bank, is backing  European Central Bank 
governing council member  Mario Draghi  as favorite to succeed
Jean-Claude Trichet as ECB president, El Pais reported.  “I consider Mario Draghi to be an excellent candidate,”
Maystadt said during an interview with El Pais, “I’ve known him
for many years and he has all the qualities necessary to be a
good and lasting president for the European Central Bank.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net  